cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Research Radar: an LLM-encoder + contextual-bandit agent for arXiv triage"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: Jiajun
    family-names: Xia
    email: jxia993@aucklanduni.ac.nz
    affiliation: University of Auckland
repository-code: "https://github.com/jxia993-hub/research-radar"
abstract: >-
  Research Radar is a small intelligent software agent that triages arXiv papers.
  A large language model encodes each paper's abstract into a structured topic
  feature vector, and a contextual-bandit reinforcement-learning policy (LinUCB /
  Linear Thompson Sampling) learns the user's preferences from save/skip feedback,
  balancing exploitation against exploration. The LLM also generates natural-language
  rationales for its recommendations. Built for COMPSCI 767 (LLM + RL).
keywords:
  - arxiv
  - contextual bandit
  - reinforcement learning
  - large language models
  - recommender system
  - intelligent agent
